For a bit more context. On the wallet UI and CNS UI. There is a config value that is set to override the scope sent in the auth request.
```window.splice_config = {
      auth: {
        algorithm: "rs-256",
        authority: "${SPLICE_APP_UI_AUTH_URL}",
        client_id: "${SPLICE_APP_UI_AUTH_CLIENT_ID}",
        token_audience: "${SPLICE_APP_UI_AUTH_AUDIENCE}",
        token_scope: "<https://ledger-api.devnet.canton.lithiumdigital.com/daml_ledger_api>",
      },```
Although at there is no ENV to set this. We were able to override the config using a configmap. But the code does handle custom scope it receives from the config.

```const openid_scope = token_scope !== 'daml_ledger_api' ? 'openid' : null;

    // We include the `offline_access` scope to tell auth0 we want refresh tokens when we first authenticate.
    // The refresh tokens are then used to automatically retrieve new access tokens before they expire without re-authenticating.
    const scope = [token_scope, openid_scope, 'offline_access'].filter(s => !!s).join(' ');

